    "description_long": "This object is a vintage-style radio receiver with a rectangular wooden body and a textured front panel. The front features a large circular tuning dial with a metallic rim, three round control knobs below it, and a mesh speaker grille. The brand name 'VICTROLA' is visible on the lower left of the front panel. Draped over the top is a red and black checkered cloth, adding a casual, lived-in appearance. The sides and back are smooth wood, while the bottom has a barcode sticker and four rubber feet for stability.",
